<br>
I don't have epic &lt;fuggin hate staff&gt;, nor do i have elemental renewal. What i really dont have is hours to LFG.<br>
<br>
I enjoy being a mage and know what we are capable of, but what i dont have is somewhere to go xp that isnt a waste of my time.<br>
<br>
Any suggestions on somewhere to go to show some gain would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Help a magi, down on his luck. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.mirrorpages.com/internet/vamppire/60sigsml.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=negaburn>negaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(11/23/02 5:39:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  ..</span><hr size=1> first , POP is not an exp paradise for soloing necros or wizards.  sure i can solo some snarable mobs with my wizard, but it's not mana effecient ( takes a while to kill and a lot of mana) plus it's dangerous. yesterday while kiting a rat in POD , a spider mob comes up up from behind me dispells me, roots me , then stacks 3 dot's and a nuke on me. i gate only to die from the dot damage.. yeah i can solo , but i prefer a partner or group for the planes.<br>
<br>
also , a lot of mobs cannot be snared in POP. which means wizards will not be soloing them.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=negaburn>negaburn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(11/23/02 5:49:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  one more thing..</span><hr size=1> i suggest making your own groups if you have trouble finding one. DON'T sit at zone in for hours til you have the &quot;perfect group&quot; of chanter , cleric, tank blah blah blah, like the morons in seb do. be creative. most mobs in POP will tear through our pets very fast, so kiting them is important.  pick up a necro , wizard, or druid to kite the mob with snare, a melee damage dealer (i prefer rogue when anger kiting). you could* get more classes but this group of 3 works well.<br>
<br>
the mob is snared, snarer gains agro by dot's or nukes, rogue backstabs, your 60 water pet backstabs. if done correctly a healer is not needed, or a main tank.<br>
<br>
just remember you don't need 6 people for a group. enjoy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 494<br> <font color=#333333>(12/25/02 5:16:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Small efficient groups are the key</span><hr size=1> The best non-standard group i've been in is Enchanter + Ranger + Mage, charm-kiting mobs.<br>
<br>
Then aggro-kiting with a Wizard + Mage or Necro + Mage<br>
<br>
Another effective group is Shaman + Mage. Shaman pulls with a slow, your pet tanks.<br>
<br>
And lets not forget the beauty that is an all-mage group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=webdaddyfresh>webdaddy fresh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(12/25/02 8:22:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: Ability to solo, where?</span><hr size=1> There are a few posts regarding PoS soloing that I'd suggest reading through if you're interested in soloing in the planes.  I haven't obtained any 3rd tier flags yet, so I can't comment on anything past PoV/PoS, but soloing really isn't that difficult.  Pet tanking is out of the question, save a few caster mobs.  That's about it really, just read through the PoS posts and try pulling with fbot and aggro kiting with the pet.  This isn't extremely effective, but it does work well on PoN spiders and the occasional tree.  <br>
<br>
Good Luck<br>
<br>
Toyorgrav<br>
61 mage<br>
Fennin Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cicelygoldenfair>cicely goldenfair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 444<br> <font color=#333333>(12/26/02 4:48:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: Ability to solo, where?</span><hr size=1> a few places i currently solo at, lvl 61 magician-<br>
<br>
akheva ruins<br>
old sebillis<br>
siren's grotto<br>
umbral plains<br>
plane of nightmare (large downtime)<br>
plane of disease (large downtime)<br>
plane of innovation (large downtime)<br>
<br>
hope this helps... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 821<br> <font color=#333333>(12/31/02 12:30:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm47.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: Ability to solo, where?</span><hr size=1> I can't say I successfully solo in any of the PoP zones, but at level 61 (and since 59 at the earliest) it has been possible for me to partner with practically ANY class and get experience in at least Tier 1 zones.<br>
<br>
I would imagine that once I get PoP level pets I could try the same in Tier 2 zones, though it would be just a little bit scarier.<br>
